WISCONSIN v. MICHIGAN. No. 12, original. Argued March 2, 3, 1936. — Mr. Adolph J. Bieberstein, with whom Mr. James E. Finnegan,- Attorney General of Wisconsin, Mr. Joseph G. Hirschberg, Deputy Attorney General, and Mr. J. E. Messer schmidt, Assistant Attorney General, were on the brief, for plaintiff. Mr. Edward A. Bilitzke, with whom Mr. David H. Crowley, Attorney General of Michigan, and Mr. James F. Shepherd, Deputy Attorney General, were on the brief, for defendant.

Decided March 16, 1936.
